# Backend Architecture

The Memor backend is built using Node.js and Express, implementing the RESTful API architecture for AI processing, subscription management, and vector database operations.

## Technology Stack
- Runtime: Node.js
- Framework: Express.js with TypeScript
- Database: Firebase Firestore
- Authentication: Firebase Auth
- Vector Database: Pinecone
- AI/ML: OpenAI, LangChain
- Security: Helmet, express-rate-limit, CORS

## Directory Structure
- [memor-backend/src/](mdc:memor-backend/src) - Source code
- [memor-backend/src/controllers/](mdc:memor-backend/src/controllers) - Request handlers
- [memor-backend/src/services/](mdc:memor-backend/src/services) - Business logic
- [memor-backend/src/middleware/](mdc:memor-backend/src/middleware) - Express middleware
- [memor-backend/src/routes/](mdc:memor-backend/src/routes) - API routes
- [memor-backend/src/utils/](mdc:memor-backend/src/utils) - Utility functions
